summary: This is a calendar entry for a scheduled call between the SDNY and the ODAG regarding the Epstein/Maxwell case, set for August 19, 2020. It indicates a high-priority, confidential coordination meeting between federal prosecutors.

events.title: SDNY-ODAG Coordination Call on Epstein/Maxwell
events.description: A scheduled 30-minute call between the U.S. Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York (SDNY) and the Office of the Deputy Attorney General (ODAG) regarding the Epstein/Maxwell case.

keyFacts: A high-priority (Priority: 5) call was scheduled between SDNY and ODAG prosecutors regarding the Epstein/Maxwell case on August 19, 2020.
The calendar entry is marked with the classification 'X-PERSONAL', indicating its confidential or sensitive nature.
The entry was created on August 18, 2020, the day before the scheduled call.
The document shows ongoing federal legal coordination in the Epstein/Maxwell case in August 2020.
The event title explicitly links the Epstein and Maxwell cases as the subject of the call.
